    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Neutrals with Blue Accent -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A 4-step wizard (SPA) structure was chosen. The source is a dense, linear process. A wizard-style interface, showing only one "Fase" (Phase) at a time, is the most user-friendly structure. It manages cognitive load, prevents users from skipping critical steps, and guides them sequentially. Navigation is handled by a top stepper-nav and bottom "Anterior"/"Próxima" buttons. This structure directly maps to the report's 4 phases but makes the content digestible and action-oriented. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
        - Report Info: "FORMATAR APAGA TUDO!" (Warning) -> Goal: Warn -> Viz/Method: High-visibility alert box (HTML/Tailwind) -> Interaction: None (static) -> Justification: Must be the first and most unmissable element.
        - Report Info: Fase 1 & 4 (Checklists) -> Goal: Inform/Organize -> Viz/Method: Interactive Accordion List (HTML/Tailwind/JS) -> Interaction: onClick to expand/collapse item details -> Justification: Converts "walls of text" into manageable, on-demand info chunks.
        - Report Info: Fase 3 (Installation Steps) -> Goal: Guide Process Flow -> Viz/Method: Vertical Stepper/Timeline (HTML/Tailwind) -> Interaction: None (visual only), critical steps highlighted in color -> Justification: Visually represents the sequence, which is crucial for a complex procedure. More intuitive than a long numbered list.
        - Report Info: Overall Process (4 Fases) -> Goal: Navigate -> Viz/Method: Stepper Nav (HTML/Tailwind) + JS -> Interaction: onClick to show/hide respective phase content blocks -> Justification: Core SPA navigation, isolates user focus to one step at a time.
        - Libraries: Vanilla JS for all interactions. Chart.js is loaded but not used, as the source content is procedural, not quantitative; no chart would add value.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
